          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-16094 mdt: improve remote subdir mount",
        "message": "LU-16094 mdt: improve remote subdir mount\n\nIf subdir is a remote directory, the subdir mount is inefficient\nbecause client can't fetch LOOKUP lock, and tries to lookup ROOT\nin each file access.\n\nThis patch includes changes on both server and client:\n* mdt_get_root() returns fileset parent FID along with fileset FID\n  if subdir is a remote directory.\n* ll_inode_revalidate() replaces parent FID and name if inode is\n  ROOT, and is a remote directory too.\n* simplify mdc_intent_lock(): it will try revalidate lock is FID is\n  sane, and if no lock found, continue lock enqueue.\n* update sanity 247f/247g, add 247h.\n\nSigned-off-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ib85674f795c1d5de0d121ef70315323af0c7fd7a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
